<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-22T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-22T04:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6188:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-22T11:00:00+02:00">October 22, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received October 22—9:09 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>1005. My 1001, October 21, 9 p.m. Following from same source:
                                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“Italian Fleet now assembling at Taranto will sail from
                                            that port the night of October 24 to attack Corfu early
                                            on morning October 25. Large numbers of parachutists are
                                            being assembled with ships and supplies at Taranto and
                                            Bari. Plans are all set and may be put into operation on
                                            a moment’s notice. Present plan for attack on 25th might
                                            be delayed until 28th for technical reasons. Russia has
                                            been promised complete control of the Dardanelles for
                                            entry into the Axis.”</p>
                                    </quote>
                                </p>
                                <p>Inform War and Navy.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>